{"type": "root", "attrs": {"icon": "SHELF/fire", "tags": "pyro"}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Bonfire"], "extent": [0, 12]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": [" Creates a bonfire simulation using the sparse pyro solver. "], "extent": [44, 112]}, {"type": "video_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "video", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [112, 120], "body": [{"type": "summary", "indent": 4, "text": ["Pyro and ember simulation in the viewport. Colorspace: ACES, Voxels Size: 0.0085."], "extent": [176, 272]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"src": "/videos/pyro/shelf/shelf_bonfire_viewport.mp4"}}, {"ext": null, "type": "video", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [272, 280], "body": [{"type": "summary", "indent": 4, "text": ["Pyro and ember simulation rendered with Karma. Colorspace: ACES, Voxels Size: 0.0085."], "extent": [333, 438]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"src": "/videos/pyro/shelf/shelf_bonfire_karma.mp4"}}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Overview"], "extent": [438, 453], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This tool sets up a sparse pyro simulation of a bonfire with addition embers."], "extent": [453, 533]}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Understanding Bonfire"], "extent": [533, 561], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The shelf tool creates a node network consisting of the following components."], "extent": [561, 641]}, {"type": "ord_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "ord", "indent": 0, "text": ["The ", {"type": "code", "text": ["bonfire/bofire_base"]}, " chain is responsible for setting up the density and velocity sources. The start of this chain controls the shape of the fire\u2019s base. You can switch out this node for another geometry object if you want to change the look of the base. For example, you could use geometry representing fire logs."], "extent": [641, 964], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The density is further modified by the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/attribnoise", "type": "link", "text": ["Attribute Noise SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/attribnoise"}, " to provide variation in the source. The ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/attribadjustvector", "type": "link", "text": ["Attribute Adjust Vector SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/attribadjustvector"}, " is used to animate the velocity source at the base over time."], "extent": [964, 1211]}], "container": true}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "ord", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["bonfire_simulation"]}, " contains the dynamics network that consumes the sources and carries out the simulation. The parameters on the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/dop/pyrosolver_sparse", "type": "link", "text": ["Sparse Pyro Solver"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/pyrosolver_sparse"}, " have the greatest influence on the speed and height of the fire."], "extent": [1211, 1458], "body": [{"type": "task_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "task", "indent": 4, "text": ["Increase the speed of the flames"], "role": "item", "extent": [1458, 1502], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Boost the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Buoyancy Scale"]}, ". "], "extent": [1540, 1588]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["This will also increase the height of the fire."], "extent": [1588, 1653]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "bf_sim_buoyancy"}}, {"ext": null, "type": "task", "indent": 4, "text": ["Change the motion of fire"], "role": "item", "extent": [1653, 1690], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Adjust the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Disturbance"]}, ", ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Shredding"]}, ", and ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Turbulence"]}, " parameters on the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Shape"]}, " tab of the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/dop/pyrosolver_sparse", "type": "link", "text": ["Sparse Pyro Solver"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/pyrosolver_sparse"}, "."], "extent": [1725, 1892]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Disturbance generically breaks up the flames, shredding redirects the velocities (creating the\n        licks), and ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Turbulence"]}, " mimics a chaotic wind."], "extent": [1892, 2055]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "bf_sim_shape"}}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "container": true}], "container": true}, {"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["bonfire_base"]}, " controls the shape of the fire\u2019s base. You can switch out this node for another geometry object if you want to change the look of the base. For example, you could use geometry representing fire logs."], "extent": [2055, 2273]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["pyrosolver_bonfire"]}, " performs the simulation. Parameters on this node have the greatest influence on the speed and height of the fire. Parameters on the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Solving"]}, " tab allow you to make the following modifications."], "extent": [2273, 2492], "body": [{"type": "task_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "task", "indent": 4, "text": ["Increase the speed of the flames"], "role": "item", "extent": [1458, 1502], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Boost the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Buoyancy Scale"]}, ". "], "extent": [1540, 1588]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["This will also increase the height of the fire."], "extent": [1588, 1653]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "bf_sim_buoyancy"}}, {"ext": null, "type": "task", "indent": 4, "text": ["Change the motion of fire"], "role": "item", "extent": [1653, 1690], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Adjust the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Disturbance"]}, ", ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Shredding"]}, ", and ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Turbulence"]}, " parameters on the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Shape"]}, " tab of the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/dop/pyrosolver_sparse", "type": "link", "text": ["Sparse Pyro Solver"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/pyrosolver_sparse"}, "."], "extent": [1725, 1892]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Disturbance generically breaks up the flames, shredding redirects the velocities (creating the\n        licks), and ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Turbulence"]}, " mimics a chaotic wind."], "extent": [1892, 2055]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "bf_sim_shape"}}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "container": true}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["pyrolook"]}, " sets the proper viewport visualization settings, as well as generates the ", {"type": "code", "text": ["Scatter"]}, " volume for rendering. However this node does not assign any shader for rendering. "], "extent": [2595, 2776]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["popnet_embers"]}, " simulates particles that are used as embers flying out from the fire. "], "extent": [2776, 2866]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["sparktrail"]}, " takes the particle simulation of the embers and generates curves from the movement of those particles to render them as embers. "], "extent": [2866, 3011]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "code", "text": ["lopnet_bonfire_with_embers"]}, " is a simple lopsetup created to demonstrate the shading of fire and embers. "], "extent": [3011, 3121]}], "container": true}, {"level": 3, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Tips"], "extent": [5280, 5291], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["For more accurate color display, use the Academy Color Encoding System (ACES). See ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/pyro/shading#aces", "type": "link", "text": ["Shading and rendering"], "fullpath": "/pyro/shading#aces", "fragment": "#aces"}, " in the Pyro chapter for information on how to set this up."], "extent": [5322, 5519]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["Add a ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/render/lights", "type": "link", "text": ["Spot Light"], "fullpath": "/render/lights"}, " for better visualization in the viewport and an ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/obj/envlight", "type": "link", "text": ["Environment Light"], "fullpath": "/nodes/obj/envlight"}, " with custom hdri map for rendering."], "extent": [5519, 5686]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["Add a small amount of sharpening on the density field to bring out a bit more detail, using the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Sharpen Volume"]}, " option in the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/pyrobakevolume", "type": "link", "text": ["Pyro Bake Volume"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/pyrobakevolume"}, "'s ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Quick Setups"]}, " dropdown menu."], "extent": [5686, 5903]}, {"blevel": 7, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["Choose the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Create Lights/Cameras"]}, " option from the Pyro Bake Volume\u2019s  ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Quick Setups"]}, " dropdown menu to quickly setup the volume for rendering with lights and cameras."], "extent": [5903, 6082]}], "container": true}], "attrs": {"id": "common_spyro_tip"}}]}], "title": ["Bonfire"], "summary": [" Creates a bonfire simulation using the sparse pyro solver. "], "included": ["/nodes/sop/pyrobakevolume", "/nodes/sop/volumevisualization", "/nodes/vop/pyroadvancedshader", "/shelf/spyro_fireball"]}